Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.08,0:01:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the bus return here after two hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.97,0:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The time has passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.08,0:01:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you walk in this way you\Nwill find a village nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.18,0:01:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.86,0:01:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that very well!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.50,0:01:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I missed you very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.45,0:01:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is my hometown...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.72,0:01:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I WANT TO SEE MY GRANDMOTHER
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.51,0:02:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop making this funny sound!\NWhat do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.38,0:02:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But I apologize for leaving\Nand forgetting our past days!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.02,0:02:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.13,0:02:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Leave immediately!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.01,0:02:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to see your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Forrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.26,0:02:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Jon Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.89,0:02:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been throughout the day\Nwhen the teacher Curry?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.32,0:02:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's your fault because you read\Nthe book until late at night!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why you overslept!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.98,0:02:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Forrest knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.06,0:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks from that window all the time so\Nshe knows all the news of the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.28,0:02:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,John, you're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry! Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw something very strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.38,0:02:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Very strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.35,0:02:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.22,0:02:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Forest act like I have\Nnever seen her before!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.32,0:02:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She seemed to be arguing with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.64,0:03:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She argued?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.51,0:03:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean Grandma Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.66,0:03:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She poured water on him\Nfrom the second floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.95,0:03:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was a warm welcome!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.82,0:03:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you left the village 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.49,0:03:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your fault because you\Nnever communicated with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.56,0:03:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty years...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For me it was short...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.25,0:03:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, I never thought of returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I can't forgive such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.97,0:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going back already?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.22,0:03:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go back for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.75,0:03:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time she will actually listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.31,0:03:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Until my mother forgives me\NI will go to rest in the monastery!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.49,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mom"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Uncle!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.16,0:03:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw this guy in front of\NGrandma Forest's house, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.88,0:03:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Grandma Forest's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.78,0:04:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Eh?\N- Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.63,0:04:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Her son?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But Grandma Forest said:\N"I don't want to see your face!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.91,0:04:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Albert left the house after\Narguing with his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he left this village
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.91,0:04:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He argued with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't seem to work today either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.47,0:04:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why Grandma Forest doesn't let him in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.32,0:04:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though he is her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Something might have happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.10,0:05:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The son of Mrs. Forest left
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,before your father came to this village so\Nwe can't anticipate the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.34,0:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever the circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he still wants to see Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.15,0:05:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.82,0:05:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.30,0:05:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this what a family does?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.06,0:05:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,John, it certainly does, but there are\Nmany circumstances in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.81,0:05:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But, is definitely a parent\NI would like to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.02,0:05:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, isn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.89,0:05:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.99,0:05:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.46,0:05:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.00,0:05:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Where are you going on your holiday?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have a short talk with Mrs. Forrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What do you mean by living together?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.26,0:05:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.07,0:05:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mrs. Forrest, just a moment!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.24,0:05:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Sam Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.81,0:06:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You came for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.01,0:06:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you watching the latest thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.61,0:06:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come in for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.32,0:06:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is this...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.15,0:06:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Enter quickly and close the door\Nso no stranger enters here!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Regardless of that...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.78,0:06:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that strange man your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My son, you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.67,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam Carraclough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.91,0:06:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.56,0:06:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any son!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.88,0:06:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My only family is my late husband George!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.60,0:06:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that I don't have any sons!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.63,0:06:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, Mrs. Forrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,F-father?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.91,0:06:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.62,0:06:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hooper, call him quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.72,0:07:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Y--yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.75,0:07:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... It has little blood pressure only!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to be not very active.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.32,0:07:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm back!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.06,0:07:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Will my grandmother come to our house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No... it seems she doesn't want to forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.99,0:07:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.49,0:07:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In this picture looks like a very nice grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I will leave your present here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.88,0:07:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}John Carraclough!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.97,0:07:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to treat me as a patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you late for the kite?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.68,0:07:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.37,0:07:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have to do it, grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.84,0:07:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still standing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:07:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.24,0:08:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you go with him, Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I always look at this part of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.29,0:08:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Duhan is here much as it is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks something good has happened to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.94,0:08:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sam Carraclough's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I still remember the first day\Nwe met in this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He was still young and went to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.95,0:08:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the day when John got you,\Nyou were a puppy, Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an old picture of our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.68,0:08:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.07,0:08:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my late husband George,\Nand this kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a beautiful day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.25,0:09:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how things
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.38,0:09:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,got even bigger until they became like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.05,0:09:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end he left the house\Nand lived freely elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,George was working hard
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to make money for my son Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But that boy stole the golden piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.97,0:09:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I didn't know how he lives\Nand where he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.65,0:09:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when his father died, he never came!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.44,0:09:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he understood his sin\Nhe came after he left this village
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask me to live with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.03,0:09:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You bastard!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whoa!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.64,0:09:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It flew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You are late, Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been to Grandma Forest all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And Grandma Forrest's son?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Lassie, did you know\Nthat about grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up, Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, someone is sitting there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wonder who is it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.92,0:10:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.91,0:10:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.16,0:10:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurt? You are wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.27,0:10:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I just lost something very precious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Very precious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.35,0:10:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's a necklace I got from my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.61,0:10:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A necklace?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.27,0:10:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very precious for my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.03,0:10:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.77,0:10:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.89,0:10:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, we have met you\Nbut we haven't asked who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.58,0:10:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.22,0:10:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Roy George Forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, could he be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Forrest's grandson?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.35,0:10:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.74,0:11:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know my grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.25,0:11:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We really know her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.97,0:11:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We know her, yet we didn't know\Nanything about grandmother's grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.10,0:11:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know, it was a novelty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.67,0:11:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.41,0:11:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.88,0:11:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I also didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.77,0:11:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,about having a grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.75,0:11:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't know anything\Nabout your grandmother
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it means that you are\Nvery terrible and stubborn...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.35,0:11:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! This is rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.39,0:11:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... right... sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.61,0:11:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is the one who\Noppressed my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to see my grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.68,0:11:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.32,0:11:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have an old picture of my grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.90,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks very nice and she smiles!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.77,0:11:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Eh?\N- Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.01,0:11:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at the picture a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.93,0:12:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to see my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Also...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.08,0:12:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Also?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't told my father and mother\Nabout coming here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.63,0:12:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you about your grandmother's place!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.79,0:12:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mom!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.86,0:12:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh!\N- Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My son and his mother want to see you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.57,0:12:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's your grandson, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.91,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you want to see him, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My grandson?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My only family is my late husband George!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't have any children!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't have any child, I mean\NI don't have any grandson!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How should I meet strangers?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Mom...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.94,0:12:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Leave!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you don't leave, I will pour water on you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandmother... don't want to see me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.51,0:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.09,0:13:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.03,0:13:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.14,0:13:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to see you, Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.22,0:13:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's a little stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.23,0:13:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she doesn't want to say\Nthat she really wants to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.12,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.36,0:13:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we do anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Listen John...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.50,0:13:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe my mother is so stubborn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Do you want to cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.67,0:13:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.06,0:13:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I left this village
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to many places and\Nstarted building my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.87,0:13:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end I stayed in a house of my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.90,0:13:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I can welcome her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I was thinking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.45,0:13:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me 20 years to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She's 20 years older!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah-ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't give up easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:14:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do that easily after\Nyou decided to leave the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I inherited this\Nfrom my mother or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.28,0:14:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My grandson?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.23,0:14:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.50,0:14:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.81,0:14:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings you to my home, John Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,E-e-eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.78,0:14:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought some cookies with me,\NI want to have tea with you, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what wind carry you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.02,0:14:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well okay, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I haven't come alone,\Nis it okay if my cousin comes with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.63,0:14:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.75,0:14:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This face...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.33,0:14:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Albert! It's not possible...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.57,0:14:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to meet her as her grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.70,0:14:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If I tell her that I'm her grandson,\Nshe'll throw me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.09,0:14:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.73,0:14:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is it okay to have tea here sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.07,0:14:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My grandmother...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.91,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your cousin, John Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.76,0:15:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The person that's with you doesn't seem to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Today he came to visit me in my house!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.06,0:15:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know that you have a cousin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? But it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}John...!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,John!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.75,0:15:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you here? You're away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're calling you, John Carraclough!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now answer them immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.32,0:15:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll go at them for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.32,0:15:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy, pour tea for grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.77,0:15:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't, Sandy calls me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.17,0:15:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go with him quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I will give you tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.09,0:15:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you stand like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to drink tea,\Nyou should bring a chair and sit on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.66,0:15:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.88,0:16:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm! Your parents souldn't\Ngive you that funny name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.56,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does this village produce coal?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather was a worker in the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.30,0:16:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.79,0:16:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was working in that mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.12,0:16:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.55,0:16:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A man was proud of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And... what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.51,0:16:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think that your father\Nis proud of your hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.16,0:16:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was a mine worker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.98,0:16:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:16:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's unfortunate!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.23,0:17:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.26,0:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Before my birth my father became a sailor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.42,0:17:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he visited many countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He was always yearning\Nfor such a life of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.98,0:17:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am shocked by his situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.99,0:17:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not looking here, it's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hear anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't seem to speak at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.09,0:17:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.01,0:17:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Colin...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn't the time to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.73,0:17:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,John's cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:17:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.91,0:18:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.05,0:18:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Don't do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.81,0:18:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lassie, let him go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}T-t-this is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.19,0:18:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Give it to me, Lassie!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.69,0:18:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,T-this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.19,0:18:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it from my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.77,0:18:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This golden piece dates back\Nto the fifteenth century!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.92,0:18:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the gold piece that George took!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.40,0:18:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How could a child like you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.69,0:18:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know anything about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.79,0:18:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because my father\Ndidn't tell me any word!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.26,0:18:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,However, regardless of the extent of poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it can't be replaced by money\Nbecause it was as precious as he said!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.37,0:18:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.87,0:18:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.25,0:18:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When my father became a sailor,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.94,0:19:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he was afflicted with serious illness and yet\Nhe worked hard to earn money for us!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.56,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...But
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But he never thought\Nof replacing this gold with money,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather did his best!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.30,0:19:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn't sold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why he worked hard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.98,0:19:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,not to forget those days!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.48,0:19:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stay there and come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.73,0:19:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because of my age I can't hear you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Come closer and talk to me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.75,0:19:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.99,0:19:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very happy because I came to this village!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.06,0:19:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,My father didn't work in the mine,\Nand became a sailor,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.13,0:19:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,yet I am still proud of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship he was working in was operated by coal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.03,0:19:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The furnace of the ship was reddening, and it\Nwas the coal that led him to the seven seas!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.68,0:19:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Charcoal xxx my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.30,0:20:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I came here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And found my grandfather here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.31,0:20:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Roy, you are... my grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.82,0:20:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.17,0:20:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you here, John Carraclough?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.52,0:20:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Show yourself immediately!{\i0}\N- Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.81,0:20:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.67,0:20:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue from Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father returned to the bus!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is still in Jones' shop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't go today as long as he thinks about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks about what he will do all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.09,0:20:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, you're wrong!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.40,0:20:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandmother, I hid him from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.26,0:20:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Albert is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been here a while\Nand he' s listening to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.53,0:20:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.85,0:20:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you tried to dismiss\Nmy theory, John Carraclough!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
